{"author":{"id":"68dfa65ee618df2786e7da658bbfbbcc1f0c757170d9426e314e5f0886bcc55d"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1615890419,"nonce":"ya/PCzrzFMTxhP9agBNkmftHVgQ=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDgwMDE0MDMwMg==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/3526#issuecomment-800140302"},"message":"Hi @yvanlebras I'm currently at stacks2 https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/pull/3510 anyway. I checked the stacks2 sources a bit:\n\n`log_fst_comp` seems to have an effect in a class `HapDivergenceExport`, i.e. add columns to some of the outputs. It appears to me that this is: - `phistats.tsv` and files of the format `out_prefix + \".phistats_\" + pop_1p.name + \"-\" + pop_2p.name + \".tsv\";` (the later ones are ignored by the tool at the moment). \n\nSo `log_fst_comp` only modifies an output but does not disable it, i.e. it should be removed from all filters.\n\nIt seems to me that `fst_summary.tsv` and `phistats_summary.tsv` are written within the same function (`LocusDivergence.write_summary`) which is called if a boolean `calc_fstats` is `true`. This boolean is enabled by the command line parameters `--smooth/-k`, `--smooth-fstats` and `--fstats` (I guess the former two just do this implicitly). \n\nIn addition the boolean controls two exports: `SnpDivergenceExport` and `HapDivergenceExport`\n\n-  `HapDivergenceExport` creates the files mentioned above.\n- `SnpDivergenceExport` creates files of the form `out_prefix + \".fst_\" + pop_1p.name + \"-\" + pop_2p.name + \".tsv\"` which we ignore at the moment\n\nSo, the filter should also check for `smooth/k` or `smooth-fstats` which implicitly also enable `fstats` (do we want to restructure the form? suggestions?)...","files":null}]}